review_blob: This one is hard to rate.  Has a golden appearance with a good Pils nose and initial taste but then its banana, honey, marzipan and spice notes.  Finishes a bit cloying.  Interesting.
beer_name: Dogfish Head Midas Touch Golden Elixir

review_blob: Bottled but not skunked, yet.  Had little aroma but a decent Pils malt flavor and no hop notes.  Its sad that this is better than Bud.

Pours a light amber with rocky white head.  Aroma is of candied orange.  Taste is sweet with hop notes of orange, grapefruit and spice followed by a solid punch of hop bitterness.  Some toasted malt notes as well.  Just perfect.
On draft at the Saucer.  Has a light golden body with faint head.  Aroma is of sweet Pils malt with some herbal hop notes.  Taste is similar, but a bit sweet.  Decent German lager.

On draft at the Saucer.  Has a light hazy, golden body with ample white head.  Aroma is of coriander and citrus.  Grainy taste with some spicy and fruity notes admixed.  Has a great mouthfeel.  Better than the regular Hoegaarden in my opinion.

Pours a light amber with slight white head.  Aroma is just like putting your nose in a bag of fresh hops!  Has notes of strong citrus (grapefruit, orange, mango) and pine as well as a significant malt presence.  The alcohol is noticable and hot, but not harsh.  There are also some spicy notes (black pepper and cardamom along with some mint).  Finishes remarkably dry despite the alcohol content.  Not excessively bitter, but truly the hoppiest beer I have ever had!

Dark brown beer with off-white head.  Light carbonation for the style.  Has a rather mild aroma with only some chocolate and dark fruits.  Taste is primarily powdered cocoa.   Couldnt really taste the raisins.  A bit too much dark malt for my taste.  Finishes too sweet.

Pours a hazy orange with rapidly diminishing white head.  Some lacing.  Has an intriguing aroma of pear, honey and spices.  Tastes phenolic with a bit of residual sweetness.  Another great beer from Unibroue.
Pours a hazy gold with quckly diminishing white head.  Has a fruity aroma.  Grainy taste with a fair bit of banana and only a hint of clove.  Thirst quenching but a little unbalanced for a hefe.

Great triple.  Has a bright golden body with giant white, fluffy head.  Leaves a wonderful lacing in the glass.  Spicy and mildy fruity aroma and taste.  Well attenuated.  Goes down a little too well if you know what I mean.

Has a light copper body with tight head.  Subtle herbal aroma.  Taste is more resinous with piney notes.  Decent malt backbone as well.  An instructive example of Columbus hops.  Although their character is difficult for me to describe, it is sufficiently unique that I can retrospectively identify other beers Ive had in the past that used them.
On tap at the Saucer.  Has a golden body with ample white head.  Aroma is of citrusy hops, largely a grapefruit note.  Taste is sweet with a mild bitterness.

Pours a light amber with thick head.  Aroma is a bit of pithy lemon and a whole lot of cat piss.  Good malty notes before the hops hit you.  Kind of rough and pungent hop flavor, like Chinook.  Sticky, resinous finish.  Not sure I care for New Zealand hops.
beer_name: Sierra Nevada Harvest Fresh Hop IPA - Southern Hemisphere

review_blob: 2007 vintage.  Pours a deep amber with abundant beige head.  Nice lacing in the glass.  Has a powerful aroma of banana, pear, rose and pepper.  Taste is similar with the addition of caramel, figs, and chocolate.  Some higher alcohol notes as well. Finishes a little sweet.
beer_name: Gouden Carolus Cuvee Van De Keizer Blauw/Blue

review_blob: Pours a nice light brown, deep amber with faint off-white head.  Has a unique bready, malty aroma.  Taste is complex with butterscotch, caramel, figs and cocoa.  Finishes with just a little sweetness.  Alcohol is well-hidden.  A great wee!

Brown beer with red highlights and a pink head.  Aroma is intense with a sweet and sour cherry note.  Also has some balsamic vinegar in there, too.  Taste is overly sweet with only a bit of acidity to balance it out.  Couldnt pick up on any real funk as one would see in a kriek.  Tastes like carbonated Nyquil.

Golden beer with ample white head.  Has little aroma other than some pear and spice.  Taste is somewhat intese with pear, banana and clove.  Notable alcohol flavor, too.  Finishes appropriately dry.  Good, but not $5 a bottle good.

beer_brewer_name: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
review_blob: Good caramel and toast character and reasonably crisp finish.  Little aroma, though.
A lovely amber beer with faint white head.  Has an aroma of noble hops and nice bready note.  Tastes of light caramel and toast.  The best Vienna lager Ive had.

The cork popped with the release of a tremendous aroma -- fruity, spicy and yeasty, almost breadlike.  Flavor is the typical Unibroue profile with lots of spicy phenolics, some stone fruits and rum raisin.  Finishes appropriately dry.  Similar to their other strong darks, just more intense.  At 10.5% abv, its probably best to share the bottle with someone else.

Pours a deep brown with red highlights and a thin off-white head.  Aroma is minimal, only some English hops.  The taste has some caramel, bread and light nutty flavors but doesnt have the almond/hazelnut intensity of sam smiths.  Decent, just let it warm up a bit first.
Slightly hazy orange with abundant Belgian lace.  Has a lovely tart aroma.  The flavor is of citrus, Brett and hay.  Finishes dry, dry, dry.  My first geuze but it wont be my last!
Has a clear, golden appearance with an ample white head.  Aroma and taste is of fruit, vanilla and cardamom.  Somewhat underattenuated.  Unusual.

Decent witbiere.  Has a startlingly clear appearance with slight white head.  Bready, yeasty aroma.  A very light fruitiness in the palate but mostly phenolic.  Finishes slightly tart.  Very carbonated.

Disappointed with this one.  The packaging made me expect a maibock but what poured out of the bottle tasted like porter.  Strong diacetyl and roasted notes.  Unlike any bock Ive ever had.  Still a good beer, just not to style.

Mahogany beer with light brown head.  Aroma is of caramel, spice.  Has a sharp caramel flavor with some licorice, chocolate and tobacco notes.  Finishes appropriately dry.  Has some unpleasant phenolic character (styrifoam) too.

Pours nicely with a golden body and frothy white head.  Aroma is of honey, of course, and indistinct spices.  Spicy taste with some light fruit (mostly banana) and a slightly sweet finish.  A new favorite.

Deep amber beer with off-white head.  Has a nice aroma of yeast, bread and caramel.  Taste is sweet with caramel and hard candy notes as well as a firm bitterness and dry roastiness, presumably from roasted barley.  There is a touch of diacetyl.  Smooth, full mouthfeel but finishes a little dry.  Not bad.

Deep amber beer with off-white head.  Aroma of grass, pine and litter box.  Very sharp, catty bitterness with a little malt background in the finish.  Resiny at the end.  I must be a mutant but I cant stand Chinook hops.  Just tastes like ass to me.

Pours a deep brown with red highlights.  Aroma is that of balsamic vinegar.  The taste is much more complex with dark fruits, caramel and licorice balanced by a thirst-quenching tartness.  Very little Brett character at all.  Finishes dry.  Flat out wonderful.

A nice middle of the road ale.  Not an American pale ale.  There is a strong malt presence here with just enough hops to balance it out.  Has a good bready, caramelly, nutty taste and aroma.  Good session beer.

Light brown beer with off-white head.  Has a muted aroma but some American hop notes are present.  Tastes bittersweet with nutty, caramel flavors.  Has a slight astringency that I dont care for.  Has a great aftertaste, though.
Copper beer with white head.  Has a malty sweet aroma and tastes of caramel, bread, nuts.  Has a smooth mouthfeel with a touch of diacetyl to round things out.

Black with a light tan head.  Has a malty aroma with some coffee and chocolate notes.  Also a good bit of diacetyl.  Taste is similar with some dark fruits.  A bit too roasty for me, though and has a an ashy finish.
Nice session ale.  Has a deep copper body with an aroma of bread, nuts.  Some caramel in the taste with a firm bitterness.
Dark copper to amber beer with fine white head.  Aroma is of nuts, caramel and great German malts.  Taste is sweet up front but well-attenuated with a slightly astringent finish.
On draft at the Saucer.  Copper beer with thick white head.  Aroma is virtually nonexistent.  Slight malty, toasty background which is overrun by resinous American hop notes.  Disappointing.

Jee, maybe I got a bad batch.  Looks nice, smells foul and tastes worse.  Has some typical pine and citrus aroma as well as some funk (and not the good kind).  Has some similar hop notes in the taste but very muddy, indistinct.  Almost like a watered down pale ale.

Pours a slightly hazy gold due to yeast sediment.  Has a small white head.  Aroma is sweet with malt.   Has a sweet taste as well with notes of honey, caramel and bread.  Little hop presence.  A decent session ale.

On draft at the Flying Saucer.  Served in a pint glass, oh well.  Has a light orange color with rich white head.  Aroma is of banana, but not overwhelmingly so.  Also note some unidentifiable citrus as well.  Tastes of banana and apricot as well as phenols (clove and styrifoam?).  Still the best hefe Ive had.

Pours a deep brown with amber hightlights and a thick beige head.  Aroma is of bananas flambe.  Also has a light smokiness.  The taste is fruity with banana again but also raisins and figs.  Some chocolate as well.

Bottle from a sealed 12 pack so not skunked.  Very pale golden beer with thin white head.  Has typical Euro lager aroma of Pils malt, maybe some spicy hop notes and a twinge of DMS.  Taste is the same.  Too carbonated with very thin mouthfeel.  Now what the hell am I going to do with the other 11 bottles?
Pours a deep amber to light brown with thick beige head.  Aroma was muted with only some banana noted.  Tastes sweet and spicy with some grape and port flavors.  Also cocoa.  Nice dry finish.

Nice deep copper beer with little aroma.  Has a nice sweet malty flavor that to my mind has a rounder, smoother caramel flavor such as from decoction mashing rather than caramel malts.  Better than I recall.
Lovely pale golden beer with an aroma of fresh hay and barley flour.  Has a lightly sweet, honeyed taste and dry finish.  Refreshing.
Nice amber beer with faint white head.  Little aroma to speak of.  Has a sweet taste with notes of molasses and spices.

Although I like the beer in general, all of their products seem to taste the same.  I would have a hard time distinguishing this one from the "blonde ale."  Quiet malt presence, a little toast and very little hop character.
A golden beer with rich white head.  Little hop aroma or flavor but nice clean bitterness.  The star here is malt, though.  Has a sweet, light caramel flavor followed by a bread-like note.

Black beer with garnet highlights.  Has an aroma of citrusy American hops.  Tastes of caramel, chocolate, coffee and tangerine.  Is fairly drinkable with little indication of the high alcohol content.
beer_name: Left Hand Wake Up Dead Imperial Stout

review_blob: Copper colored beer with thin head and light carbonation.  Has a strong aroma of pine, citrus and spice.  Similar taste along with some caramel and mint.  Some notes of sherry too.  Reasonably drinkable for 9% abv.
